{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783148447493,"sessionID":"ses_0d42abee0ffevTP1InSH4JHVlk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"tool_GXNscvZzGVhSZi5McDv8nbsY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Detached deep-review fan-out","subagent_type":"general","prompt":"You are a detached deep-review lineage orchestrator executing a 10-iteration review loop as an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage. Do not delegate to other agents; execute directly. Do not use the Task tool.\n\n**MANDATORY BOUNDARIES**\n- Write ONLY inside `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin/review/lineages/kimi-review`.\n- Do not read, write, edit, or delete any path outside that directory, except to READ the review target files under `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin`.\n- Target files are READ-ONLY. Do not modify code or spec docs under review.\n\n**PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS** (emit these as BINDING lines before any writes):\n```\nBINDING: review_target=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin\nBINDING: review_target_type=spec-folder\nBINDING: review_dimensions=correctness,security,traceability,maintainability\nBINDING: spec_folder=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin\nBINDING: execution_mode=AUTONOMOUS\nBINDING: lineage_mode=auto\nBINDING: artifact_dir=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin/review/lineages/kimi-review\nBINDING: session_id=fanout-kimi-review-1783146823455-7q45s6\n```\n\n**REVIEW PARAMETERS**\n- spec_folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin`\n- artifact_dir: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin/review/lineages/kimi-review`\n- session_id: `fanout-kimi-review-1783146823455-7q45s6`\n- loop_type: `review`\n- stopPolicy: `max-iterations`\n- maxIterations: `10`\n- convergenceThreshold: `0.1`\n- executor: `cli-opencode model=kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (record in state; if the CLI is not available in this environment, perform the iteration review directly with available Read/Grep/Glob/code_graph_query tools and note the executor fallback in the JSONL `executor` audit block).\n\n**REQUIRED READING BEFORE START**\n1. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md`\n2. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\n3. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md`\n4. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md`\n5. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n6. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n7. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`\n8. `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/032-goal-opencode-plugin/spec.md`\n\n**WORKFLOW TO EXECUTE**\n\n1. **phase_init**\n   - Create `{artifact_dir}/iterations/`, `{artifact_dir}/prompts/`, `{artifact_dir}/deltas/`, `{artifact_dir}/logs/` if needed.\n   - Write `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with the parameters above, mode `review`, status `initialized`, releaseReadinessState `in-progress`, lineageMode `new`, generation `1`, continuedFromRun `null`, parentSessionId `null`, reviewDimensions `[\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]`, crossReference core `[\"spec_code\",\"checklist_evidence\"]` and overlay `[\"feature_catalog_code\",\"playbook_capability\"]`.\n   - Write `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` first record as the config record.\n   - Write `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty open/resolved/repeated findings, dimensionCoverage all false, findingsBySeverity P0/P1/P2 zero, convergenceScore 0.\n   - Write `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from the template structure in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md` (read it). Include: topic, review-dimensions checklist, completed-dimensions, running-findings, files-under-review table, cross-reference-status, known-context, review-boundaries, next-focus.\n   - Note: `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` likely does not exist; set `resource_map_present: false` and record the skip note.\n\n2. **phase_main_loop** — repeat until 10 iterations have completed.\n   - Treat any convergence vote before iteration 10 as telemetry only; do NOT stop early. If convergence signals are strong, broaden the review angle (e.g., deeper file-level review, cross-phase traceability, edge cases, regression test coverage, doc drift) rather than synthesizing.\n   - For each iteration N (001..010):\n     a. Read current JSONL, registry, strategy, config.\n     b. Determine next focus dimension, rotating through correctness, security, traceability, maintainability and broadening angles as dimensions repeat. Maintain a deterministic order for breadth:\n        - 001 correctness (spec-vs-code claims)\n        - 002 security (input validation, secrets, trust boundaries)\n        - 003 traceability (spec_code + checklist_evidence protocols)\n        - 004 maintainability (tests, docs, dead code)\n        - 005 correctness (edge cases / error handling)\n        - 006 security (lifecycle / autonomy safety)\n        - 007 traceability (cross-phase references)\n        - 008 maintainability (naming, exports, test architecture)\n        - 009 correctness (plugin command routing)\n        - 010 maintainability (doc/spec drift + polish)\n     c. Review target files relevant to that focus. Target scope is the spec folder and its child phases, especially the implemented plugin `.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js`, command `.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md`, tests `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-state.test.cjs`, and spec-kit references. Do NOT modify them.\n     d. Write `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` with the structure from state_format.md. It MUST end with exactly one line: `Review verdict: PASS`, `Review verdict: CONDITIONAL`, or `Review verdict: FAIL`.\n     e. Append exactly ONE JSONL record to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with all required fields: `type: iteration`, `iteration`, `mode: review`, `sessionId`, `status`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails` (each with severity, category, file, line, title, description, content_hash, findingClass, evidenceRefs), `newFindingsRatio`, `traceabilityChecks` when applicable, `executor` audit block, timestamp.\n     f. Update `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` to reflect completed dimension, running findings, what-worked/what-failed, next-focus.\n     g. Regenerate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` and `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` from the JSONL history (you may implement a minimal deterministic reducer or update fields by hand; the files must be consistent with JSONL).\n     h. If any new P0/P1 finding is introduced, include a typed claim-adjudication packet inside the iteration file and record `claim_adjudication` event in JSONL.\n     i. Compute newFindingsRatio using severity weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1, refinements at 0.5 multiplier. If a new P0 appears, floor ratio at 0.50.\n     j. If convergence math would vote STOP before iteration 10, append a `blocked_stop` or `stop_decision` event explaining that max-iterations policy overrides it, and continue.\n\n3. **phase_synthesis**\n   - After iteration 010, read all iteration files and JSONL.\n   - Deduplicate findings (by file + line + root cause) and assign final IDs F001, F002, ...\n   - Write `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` with all 9 core sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix. Omit Resource Map Coverage Gate (resource_map_present is false).\n   - Append synthesis event to JSONL with type `event`, event `synthesis_complete`, totalIterations 10, verdict, activeP0/P1/P2, dimensionCoverage, stopReason `maxIterationsReached`.\n   - Update config status to `complete`.\n   - Optionally run `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json '<summary>' {spec_folder}` for continuity save. If the script is unavailable, skip and note it in the audit appendix.\n\n**OUTPUT VERIFICATION**\nBefore finishing, verify these files exist and are non-empty:\n- `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json`\n- `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n- `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md`\n- `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-001.md` through `iteration-010.md`\n- `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`\n\n**FINAL MESSAGE**\nReturn a concise summary containing:\n- Verdict (PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL)\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts\n- Stop reason\n- A list of the iteration files created\n- Any errors or skipped steps\n\nDo NOT output `FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:kimi-review` yourself — the parent orchestrator will emit that line after you report success.","command":"Detached deep-review fan-out"},"output":"<task id=\"ses_0d428424cffe35oqA0SQgYg1kt\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\n**Review complete.**\n\n- **Verdict:** CONDITIONAL\n- **Active findings:** P0=0, P1=3, P2=34\n- **Stop reason:** maxIterationsReached\n- **Iteration files created:** `iterations/iteration-001.md` through `iterations/iteration-010.md`\n\n**Notes / skipped steps:**\n- `cli-opencode` executor was unavailable; review ran directly with native Read/Grep/Glob tools (recorded in JSONL `executor` audit blocks).\n- `resource-map.md` was absent, so the Resource Map Coverage Gate was skipped.\n- `generate-context.js` ran and refreshed `graph-metadata.json`, but emitted a vector-index corruption warning and skipped full semantic indexing (recorded in audit appendix).\n- One `stop_decision` event was inserted after iteration 008 because convergence signals voted STOP, then overridden by the max-iterations policy.\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_0d42abee0ffevTP1InSH4JHVlk","sessionId":"ses_0d428424cffe35oqA0SQgYg1kt","model":{"modelID":"k2p7","providerID":"kimi-for-coding"},"truncated":false},"title":"Detached deep-review fan-out","time":{"start":1783146986933,"end":1783148447486}},"id":"prt_f2bd7380e001IS38Eaz4fBZQnu","sessionID":"ses_0d42abee0ffevTP1InSH4JHVlk","messageID":"msg_f2bd6fc7c001T8JY47uZEmxgcb"}}
